      "content": "it's easy to say \"shadow groups don't exist\" when you're sitting behind a firewall, but history is full of agencies that privatized their intelligence assets long ago. they don't need law enforcement's permission to look at pattern metadata. the \"standard\" channels are exactly what they use to maintain their net. if i follow your \"transparent\" advice, i'm just handing them a map to my location. if you can't help with the technical side of breaking patterns, can you at least explain how a sophisticated actor with access to transaction metadata would typically go about identifying a target? i need to know what they're looking for so I can avoid it.",
